text: Una giornata qualunque in quest'autunno novembrile, quando la natura d√† il pi√π bel spettacolo di s√© stessa. Non pi√π il cielo terso scolorito dall'afa e il mare immobile, non pi√π i colori sbiaditi da un sole atroce che non abbronza ma brucia. Ora la luce √® tagliente, accende i contrasti tra il blu profondo del mare e il giallo del calcare della scogliera; il cielo, denso di nuvole in corsa, disegna ombre su un mare risvegliato da un lungo sonno, che respira forte contro le rocce nell‚Äôattimo in cui un‚Äôonda si infrange alta sugli scogli, come se ogni onda volesse incidere una parola sul bordo delle pietre. A tratti il vento si alza, increspa la superficie dell‚Äôacqua; nelle pozze tra gli scogli resta una schiuma sottile, memoria effimera del passaggio delle onde. Pi√π che semplici vedute, queste immagini sono punti di ascolto: invitano a sentire il rumore del mare, il fruscio del vento, il peso delle storie non dette che abitano ancora le pietre di questo che fu un ameno luogo, perch√© la fotografia √® bugiarda, ti consegna solo l‚Äôimbeccata del fotografo. Basta spostare di poco lo sguardo e il quadro cambia. Alla mia destra la lunga striscia d‚Äôasfalto della bretella per l‚Äôaeroporto taglia il territorio con il suo flusso continuo di auto. Alle mie spalle il complesso della ‚ÄúTonnara dell‚ÄôUrsa‚Äù veglia su questo teatro naturale come un‚Äôantica sentinella di pietra, ponte silenzioso tra ieri e oggi. Dietro ancora, la fila di muri, recinzioni e case sul demanio continua a raccontare una storia di occupazioni, abusi e silenzi: la stessa che denunciammo con le mostre fotografiche ‚ÄúMafia e territorio‚Äù insieme a #peppinoimpastato a #radioaut All‚Äôorizzonte la Punta del Ra√¨s continua a vegliare ed esistere in filigrana, dietro il nome ufficiale dedicato ai giudici uccisi dalla mafia, a ricordare che la toponomastica, come la memoria, cambia ma non si cancella. #fotografia #panorama #mare #paolochirco #iphone

text: iDescriptor: "Uma ferramenta de gerenciamento de dispositivos iDevice gratuita, de c√≥digo aberto e multiplataforma"Rapaz, como esperei por um app assim! Uso Linux e tenho um iPad Air (A1475) rodando iOS 12.5.At√© ent√£o, s√≥ conseguia transferir arquivos via Wi-Fi com um app chamado Phone Drive Pro que drenava a bateria e fazia o aparelho esquentar excessivamente.Com esse iDescriptor, basta ligar o cabo e fim! Ele mostra as informa√ß√µes do aparelho, incluindo sa√∫de da bateria. Tamb√©m lista os apps instalados, permitindo navegar pelos arquivos de alguns deles. E √© poss√≠vel at√© mesmo abrir imagens e rodar v√≠deos que est√£o no aparelho.Possui outras fun√ß√µes (ver abas superiores na imagem), mas verei com mais calma depois.ATEN√á√ÉO: na aba Toolbox, h√° uma op√ß√£o "Recovery Mode". N√£o clique nela sem necessidade. H√° uma Issue (#21) no GitHub de um cara que clicou nisso e "brickou" o aparelho. Disseram que aparece um alerta antes, mesmo assim √© bom avisar para evitar acidentes. Das outras fun√ß√µes que testei, tem tamb√©m o espelhamento de tela e deixar montada a unidade de armazenamento.https://github.com/iDescriptor/iDescriptor#iDescriptor #iPad #iPadAir #iPhone #iPod #iDevice #Apple #iTunes #FOSS
text_en: iDescriptor: "A free iDevice tool, open code and multiplatform," as I expected for some of them! I use Linux and have an iPad Air (A1475) around iOS 12.5. Until then, I can only transfer files via Wi-Fi with an app called Phone Drive Pro that drains the battery and makes the device forget too. With this iDescriptor, it shows the device's information, including the battery's health. It's also allowed to open some of them. It's possible to open images and turn them off.

text: Fr, it‚Äôs quite impressive how performant my #iPhone 11 still is after upgrading to #iOS 26. Used/old model (but brand new) iPhones could be had for relatively cheap (vs worse quality/featured #Android phones), so it‚Äôs good to know that you could still recommend the 11, if they couldn‚Äôt get 12 or newer.The whole ‚Äò#Apple products are expensive shtick‚Äô is outdated - you could get a #MacBook Air M1, brand new, for ~2.5k MYR or so. The other day, I even saw MacBook Air M2 (again, brand new) for ~3k MYR. These are incredibly powerful laptops with amazing screen and keyboard, a couple of #Thunderbolt/#USB4 ports, and a battery that lasts you a day if not more (I literally just charge my M1 once a week, on light use).In comparison, my sister got some #Microsoft Surface laptop, on sale, for over 3k MYR and that shit is not even half as usable as the M1, does not even have a single Thunderbolt port (which was shocking to me), and has no ‚Äòcreature comforts‚Äô either like an HDMI port - which was an issue, not having Thunderbolt.

author: irfan@sakurajima.social
text: While video conferencing, for example, you couldn't record both the system audio (i.e. the call) and your voice at the same time on #iPhone/#iOS, huh?I saw that they added something called Local Capture on iOS 26 - which adds the ability to record your audio while you're in a call, which Voice Memo couldn't for some reason, but that feature does not record your system audio at all - just your mic input.Also Local Capture records audio-only sessions as video, so if you need to share said audio as a voice note, for example, you'll need to extract the audio first. Fortunately, this is easy to do using #Apple Shortcuts. It is pretty weird for this feature not to come to iOS 18 tho, seeing it's still supported.
text_en: While video conferencing, for example, you couldn't record both the system audio (i.e. the call) and your voice at the same time on #iPhone/#iOS, huh?I saw that they added something called Local Capture on iOS 26 - which adds the ability to record your audio while you're in a call, which Voice Memo couldn't for some reason, but that feature does not record your system audio at all - just your mic input.Also Local Capture records audio-only sessions as video, so if you need to share said audio as a voice note, for example, you'll need to extract the audio first. Fortunately, this is easy to do using #Apple Shortcuts. It is pretty weird for this feature not to come to iOS 18 tho, seeing it's still supported.

author: victor@typo.social
text: I‚Äôve seen many people inaccurately state that the anodization process Apple uses to color the aluminum iPhone is a film, and that is wears away over time. It is an electrochemical process that converts the surface into aluminum oxide, and can only be scratched/chipped to expose the aluminum underneath. Harsh acidic chemicals can cause discoloration. The oleophobic coating on the screen is a film atop the glass, and it does wear away over time from being constantly touched. üì±üë®üèª‚Äçüíª#Apple #iPhone

author: irfan@sakurajima.social
text: I'm still anxiously waiting for this to progress lol - so far, doesn't seem like #Apple is doing anything to block this 'integration'. What I'm most curious about, is what #Google/#Qualcomm 's plan is to spread this new 'ability'.Will we get it through a software update? If so, will manufacturers lock it behind the latest version of #Android, or backport it to older versions? Will my 'ancient by Android standards' #Nothing Phone 1 get it?I do hope they plan to not gatekeep this and spread it as far and wide as possible, if they're trying to 'emulate' how common and widespread #AirDrop has been for #iPhone and other Apple devices, since forever ago now. Otherwise, it'd be pretty useless in the next ~5 years (at least), since Android phones in the real world are easily outdated (i.e. don't have access to the latest software version).RE: https://sakurajima.social/notes/afbq2wpyu7
